    <abstract>
      <t>The IETF has many new initiatives relying on IPv6 Enhanced Headers added in transit: SRv6, SFC, BIERv6, iOAM. Additionally, some recent developments are overlays (SRv6, VxLAN) over IPv6. It could create oversized packets that need to be dealt with. This document analyzes available standards for the resolution of oversized packet drops.</t>
